### Request 10: Retrieve all
### Response
### Status Code: 200 
### Body: A JSON array with the 4 objects, one for each exercise we created
###         Each exercise must have the following properties with the correct values
###             "_id", "name", "reps", "weight", "unit", "date"
##          Optionally exercise objects may have the property "_v"
GET http://localhost:3000/exercises HTTP/1.1


### Request 11: Retrieve Deadlift on date 07-18-24 by ID
### Response
### Status Code: 200
### Body: JSON object (not array) for the exercise with all the properties with correct values
###         "_id": ...
###         "name": "Deadlift"
###         "reps": 12
###         "weight": 30
###         "unit": "kgs"
###         "date": "07-18-24"
###     Optionally the property _v can be included
GET  http://localhost:3000/exercises/{{DEADLIFT_ID}} HTTP/1.1


### Request 12: Retrieve for non-existent ID
### Response
### Status Code: 404
### Body: {"Error": "Not found"}
GET  http://localhost:3000/exercises/{{NON_EXISTENT_EXERCISE_ID}} HTTP/1.1


### Request 13: Update exercise Deadlift with date 07-18-24
### Set reps to 20 and unit to "lbs" (name, weight and date remain unchanged)
### Response Status Code: 200
### Body: JSON object (not array) for the updated exercise with all the properties with correct values
###         "_id": ...
###         "name": "Deadlift"
###         "reps": 20
###         "weight": 30
###         "unit": "lbs"
###         "date": "07-18-24"
###     Optionally the property _v can be included
PUT http://localhost:3000/exercises/{{DEADLIFT_ID}} HTTP/1.1
content-type: application/json

{
    "name": "Deadlift",
    "reps": 20,
    "weight": 30,
    "unit": "lbs",
    "date": "07-18-24"
}

### Request 14: Verify that the previous update set reps to 20 and unit
###     to lbs (weight remains 30 and date remains 07-18-24)
### Response
### Status Code: 200
### Body: JSON object (not array) for the exercise with at least the properties
###         "_id": ...
###         "name": "Deadlift"
###         "reps": 20
###         "weight": 30
###         "unit": "lbs"
###         "date": "07-18-24"
###     Optionally the property _v can be included
GET http://localhost:3000/exercises/{{DEADLIFT_ID}} HTTP/1.1


